  <!-- WHAT TO KNOW -->
  <div class="know-section">
    <div class="section-label">WHAT TO KNOW BEFORE BUYING A DOUBLE DOOR REFRIGERATOR</div>
    <p class="know-intro">
      A good double door refrigerator gives you separate temperature control for fridge and freezer, significantly better food freshness than single-door models, and frost-free operation so you never manually defrost. In India, you can get excellent double door refrigerators from ₹22,000 to ₹50,000 covering families from 2 to 6+ people.
    </p>
    <div class="know-grid">
      <div class="know-item">
        <div class="know-icon">⭐</div>
        <div class="know-title">BEE Star Rating</div>
        <div class="know-text">5-star models save ₹8,000–10,000/year on electricity vs 2-star. Always go 3-star minimum. The LG 322L at 5-star is the most efficient in India under ₹35,000.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="know-item">
        <div class="know-icon">🔄</div>
        <div class="know-title">Inverter Compressor</div>
        <div class="know-text">All double door refrigerators in 2026 should have an inverter compressor. It auto-adjusts speed, saves energy, runs quieter, and lasts longer than conventional compressors.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="know-item">
        <div class="know-icon">📏</div>
        <div class="know-title">Capacity Guide</div>
        <div class="know-text">2 people: 250–280L. 3–4 people: 300–360L. 5+ people: 380L+. Don't undersize — you'll feel it within a year when the fridge feels packed every week.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="know-item">
        <div class="know-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="know-title">Twin Cooling vs Single Cooling</div>
        <div class="know-text">Samsung's Twin Cooling uses separate evaporators for fridge and freezer. No odour mixing, better humidity for vegetables, drier freezer. Worth the premium if you store lots of fresh produce.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="know-item">
        <div class="know-icon">🔧</div>
        <div class="know-title">After-Sales Service</div>
        <div class="know-text">Samsung and LG have India's best service networks. Whirlpool strong in metros. Haier still improving in Tier-2/3 cities. Check authorised centres in your city before buying.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="know-item">
        <div class="know-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="know-title">Indian Summer Performance</div>
        <div class="know-text">Indian summers hit 45°C+. Look for compressors rated to operate up to 43°C ambient temperature. Samsung, LG and Whirlpool inverter compressors handle Indian summers well.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HOW TO CHOOSE YOUR BUDGET -->
